ng the vector fields of the ODEs to align with empirically derived Granger-causal directions, ensuring that predicted flows (e.g., volume drop → price spike) are physically plausible over time. This fusion of continuous-time representation learning, modular graph decomposition, and causal geometric constraints introduces a fundamentally new paradigm for modeling economic spatio-temporal systems.

